so IR, could you please do that?

Also, Firefox left me Hysteria untill she gets back. I can forward 
the email if anyone wants to see it.


--- In nbwrpg@y..., "FIRE FOX" <firefox_y2k@h...> wrote:
> (I'll post CF damage now, but I won't be home over the weekend. I'm 
going to 
> Boston for the next four days (Fri-Mon) I'll be able to post again 
on 
> Tuesday. Until then, happy posting!)
> 
> Hysteria:
> 
> Hysteria, not recieving a reply from IR, assumed the situation had 
become 
> rather extreme. She reinforced the shields with what little extra 
power 
> remained and turned to run down the hall just as the ship shook 
from the 
> force of The Brotherhood's combined attacks:
> 
> CF comp: Shields at 85% and holding
> 
> Hysteria stopped midway down the hall and opened a compartment 
neatly 
> concealed behind a large panel. She grabbed a box of equipment and 
took off 
> down the CF. The pitiful mew of something caught her attention. SHe 
knew she 
> didn't have the time to stop, but looked up anyway. It was the 
kitten IR had 
> been carrying earlier. Hysteria sighed, then shouted up to it:
> 
> "C'mon cat. I'll take you to IR."
> 
> Hysteria cast it one last glance over her shoulder and then 
continued down 
> the hall. It was up to the cat whether or not it followed. She 
eventually 
> made her way up several levels until she came to a ladder. She 
climbed up, 
> and hoisted the large case over her head as she simultaneuosly 
pushed open 
> the hatch leading to the top of the CF and climbed out.
